

Here's what I did in order to overload UserController from ZfcUser:

    Create my own module (ZfcUserExt) and new controller (UserController) extending the ZfcUser\Controller\UserController;
    Just create the actions you want to overload, say registerAction;
    In module.config.php, make your new controller ('ZfcUserExt\Controller\UserController') invokable, and overload the zfcuser child_routes 'register' to call the new controller;
    Create a copy of the register view script under view\zfc-user-ext\user\;

Here're some of the code changes I have:

//module.config.php

    'view_manager' => array
    (
        'template_path_stack' => array
        (
            'zfc-user-ext-views' => __DIR__ . '/../view',
        ),
    ),

    'controllers' => array
    (
        'invokables' => array
        (
            'zfcuserext' => 'ZfcUserExt\Controller\UserController',
        ),
    ),


    'router' => array
    (
        'routes' => array
        (
            'zfcuser' => array
            (
                'options' => array
                (
                    'route' => '/account',
                    'defaults' => array
                    (
                        'controller' => 'zfcuserext',
                    ),
                ),
                'child_routes' => array
                (
                    'register' => array
                    (
                        'options' => array
                        (
                            'defaults' => array
                            (
                                'controller' => 'zfcuserext',
                            ),
                        ),
                    ),
                ),
            ),
        ),
    ),

